tps://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=BLEURT:+Learning+Robust+Metrics+for+Text+Generation&author=Sellam,+T.&author=Das,+D.&author=Parikh,+A.P.&publication_year=2020&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B39-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='39.'>Zhang, T.; Kishore, V.; Wu, F.; Weinberger, K.Q.; Artzi, Y. BERTScore: Evaluating Text Generation with BERT. <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2019</b>, arXiv:1904.09675. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=BERTScore:+Evaluating+Text+Generation+with+BERT&author=Zhang,+T.&author=Kishore,+V.&author=Wu,+F.&author=Weinberger,+K.Q.&author=Artzi,+Y.&publication_year=2019&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B40-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='40.'>Boratko, M.; Padigela, H.; Mikkilineni, D.; Yuvraj, P.; Das, R.; McCallum, A.; Chang, M.; Fokoue-Nkoutche, A.; Kapanipathi, P.; Mattei, N.; et al. A Systematic Classification of Knowledge, Reasoning, and Context within the ARC Dataset. <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2018</b>, arXiv:1806.00358. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+Systematic+Classification+of+Knowledge,+Reasoning,+and+Context+within+the+ARC+Dataset&author=Boratko,+M.&author=Padigela,+H.&author=Mikkilineni,+D.&author=Yuvraj,+P.&author=Das,+R.&author=McCallum,+A.&author=Chang,+M.&author=Fokoue-Nkoutche,+A.&author=Kapanipathi,+P.&author=Mattei,+N.&author=et+al.&publication_year=2018&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B41-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='41.'>Zellers, R.; Holtzman, A.; Bisk, Y.; Farhadi, A.; Choi, Y. HellaSwag: Can a Machine Really Finish Your Sentence? <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2019</b>, arXiv:1905.07830. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=HellaSwag:+Can+a+Machine+Really+Finish+Your+Sentence?&author=Zellers,+R.&author=Holtzman,+A.&author=Bisk,+Y.&author=Farhadi,+A.&author=Choi,+Y.&publication_year=2019&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B42-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='42.'>Hendrycks, D.; Burns, C.; Basart, S.; Zou, A.; Mazeika, M.; Song, D.; Steinhardt, J. Measuring Massive Multitask Language Understanding. <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2020</b>, arXiv:2009.03300. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Measuring+Massive+Multitask+Language+Understanding&author=Hendrycks,+D.&author=Burns,+C.&author=Basart,+S.&author=Zou,+A.&author=Mazeika,+M.&author=Song,+D.&author=Steinhardt,+J.&publication_year=2020&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B43-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='43.'>Lin, S.; Hilton, J.; Evans, O. TruthfulQA: Measuring How Models Mimic Human Falsehoods. <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2021</b>, arXiv:2109.07958. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=TruthfulQA:+Measuring+How+Models+Mimic+Human+Falsehoods&author=Lin,+S.&author=Hilton,+J.&author=Evans,+O.&publication_year=2021&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li><li id='B44-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='44.'>Sakaguchi, K.; Bras, R.L.; Bhagavatula, C.; Choi, Y. Winogrande: An Adversarial Winograd Schema Challenge at Scale. <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2021</b>, arXiv:1907.10641. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Winogrande:+An+Adversarial+Winograd+Schema+Challenge+at+Scale&author=Sakaguchi,+K.&author=Bras,+R.L.&author=Bhagavatula,+C.&author=Choi,+Y.&publication_year=2021&journal=arXiv&doi=10.1145/3474381" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>] [<a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3474381" class='cross-ref' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>CrossRef</a>]</li><li id='B45-applsci-15-01430' class='html-xx' data-content='45.'>Cobbe, K.; Kosaraju, V.; Bavarian, M.; Chen, M.; Jun, H.; Kaiser, L.; Plappert, M.; Tworek, J.; Hilton, J.; Nakano, R.; et al. Training Verifiers to Solve Math Word Problems. <span class='html-italic'>arXiv</span> <b>2021</b>, arXiv:2110.14168. [<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Training+Verifiers+to+Solve+Math+Word+Problems&author=Cobbe,+K.&author=Kosaraju,+V.&author=Bavarian,+M.&author=Chen,+M.&author=Jun,+H.&author=Kaiser,+L.&author=Plappert,+M.&author=Tworek,+J.&author=Hilton,+J.&author=Nakano,+R.&author=et+al.&publication_year=2021&journal=arXiv" class='google-scholar' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Google Scholar</a>]</li></ol></section><section  id='Tables' type='display-objects'><div class="html-table-wrap"
  id="applsci-15-01430-t001"
  
  data-position="float"
>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_td">
    <div class="html-tablepopup html-tablepopup-link" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/15/3/1430/display"
  href='#table_body_display_applsci-15-01430-t001'>
        <img data-lsrc="https://pub.mdpi-res.com/img/table.png" />
       <a class="html-expand html-tablepopup" data-counterslinkmanual = "https://www.mdpi.com/2076-3417/15/3/1430/display"
  href="#table_body_display_applsci-15-01430-t001"></a>
    </div>

  </div>
  <div class="html-table_wrap_discription">
    <b>Table 1.</b>
    Summary of Prompt Engineering techniques.
  </div>
</div>
<div class="html-table_show  mfp-hide " id="table_body_display_applsci-15-01430-t001">
  

      <div class="html-caption"><b>Table 1.</b>
    Summary of Prompt Engineering techniques.</div>
      <table >
        <thead  ><tr  ><th align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin;border-top:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Techniques</th><th align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin;border-top:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Key Characteristics</th></tr></thead><tbody  ><tr  ><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >ICL [<a href="#B13-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">13</a>,<a href="#B19-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">19</a>,<a href="#B20-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">20</a>,<a href="#B21-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">21</a>,<a href="#B22-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">22</a>,<a href="#B23-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">23</a>]</td><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Focuses on few-shot learning by providing demonstrations within prompts. Includes derivatives such as PICL (contextual data collection and reconstruction), MetaICL (continual training phase), KATE (demonstration example selection), SG-ICL (format of demonstrations), and GlobalE&amp;LocalE (demonstration order).</td></tr><tr  ><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >CoT [<a href="#B30-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">30</a>,<a href="#B31-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">31</a>]</td><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Encourages intermediate reasoning steps for solving complex problems. Demonstrated to improve logical reasoning capabilities in LLMs.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Self-Consistency [<a href="#B31-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">31</a>]</td><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Optimizes the model to produce consistent and reliable outputs across varied inputs conveying the same meaning.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >SSR [<a href="#B31-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">31</a>]</td><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Promotes systematic problem-solving by explicitly breaking down the reasoning process into individual steps.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >ToT [<a href="#B17-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">17</a>,<a href="#B31-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">31</a>]</td><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Represents reasoning as a tree structure with branches exploring diverse hypotheses or possibilities, aiding in logical exploration and plausibility evaluation.</td></tr><tr  ><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >RAG [<a href="#B24-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">24</a>,<a href="#B25-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">25</a>,<a href="#B26-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">26</a>,<a href="#B27-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">27</a>,<a href="#B28-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">28</a>,<a href="#B29-applsci-15-01430" class="html-bibr">29</a>]</td><td align='left' valign='middle' style='border-bottom:solid thin' class='html-align-left' >Addresses hallucination issues by retrieving external information (e.g., from knowledge graphs or search engines) and augmenting prompts with this information. Includes variants such as the LLM-Augmenter (retrieval before generation), Knowledge Retrieval (retrieval during generation), RARR (retrieval after generation), and CoVe (self-refinement via feedback).</td></tr></tbody>
      </table>



</div>
